------------
RDF surfaces
------------

RDF surfaces are declared using log:npn "not (positve and negative)"

    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 _:bng_2).

    _:bng_1 {
        triples
    }

    _:bng_2 {
        triples
    }

Declaring a positive surface:

    # the triples in _:bng_2 are true
    # (graffiti) log:npn (true _:bng_2).

Declaring a negative surface:

    # the triples in _:bng_1 are false
    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 false).

Declaring an implication:

    # the triples in _:bng_1 imply the triples in _:bng_2
    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 _:bng_2).

Declaring a component:

    # the triple in _:bng_2 is implied  by the triples in _:bng_1
    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 _:bng_2).
    _:bng_2 a log:Component.

Declaring a query:

    # the question triples in _:bng_1 give the answer triples in _:bng_2
    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 _:bng_2).
    _:bng_2 a log:Answer.
